  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Purpose&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Rework Rate is an indicator or the effectiveness of the team at maintaining the application. It can also indicate the&#xD;
    quality of the solution and the degree to which meets the solution requirements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Definition&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Rework rate is the number of successful deployments that transition from validation (testing) into production as a&#xD;
    percentage of all deployment attempts:&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Rework Rate = (Total packages failing verification/deployment/Total packages promoted from out of development) x 100&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Analysis&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Rework rate should be monitored over time. An increasing rework rate can indicate any of the following issues:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Unclear requirements&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Limited team/ stakeholder collaboration&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Lack of team experience or technical skills&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Architectural issues with the existing solution and a need to consider modernization&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Declining capability of the team to support the solution&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Inadequate testing effort&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Limitations in the software delivery tools or procedures&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Frequency and reporting&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Rework rate should be monitored on an ongoing basis, and made easily available to project managers, production&#xD;
    management.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Collection and reporting tools&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Rework rate can be derived from IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; ClearQuest&amp;reg; or IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Team Concert&amp;reg;. The products would be&#xD;
    configured to record state changes analogous to &quot;re-open&quot;. This is state is available in most of the ClearQuest schemas&#xD;
    and RTCz process templates. No special customizations to either tool are necessary.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Pitfall, advice and countermeasures&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Rework rate needs to be monitored constantly. You can use increasing rework rate on a component as a predictor of when&#xD;
    the component is nearing the end of its effective life, i.e. when the costs of maintenance exceed or will soon exceed&#xD;
    the value returned to the business.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    As that point is reached, modernization strategies such as re-design, or re-implementation should be considered.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
